result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody A. Miller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Report to County Jail (10 Days +), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.425(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant shall submit to a DNA sample at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department. The costs have been paid from defendant's bond.

The jail sentence shall be served with huber and good time.  The jail sentence is to begin immediately and is consecutive to any other sentence.    The defendant shall pay all sheriff and jail fees or costs allowed or imposed by law and the sheriff shall be entitled to a judgment against the defendant for any such unpaid fees or costs.  

Jail can be served in any county in the State of Wisconsin provided arrangements are made by counsel or the defendant, it is approved by the Taylor County Jail, and at no additional cost to Taylor County.
Consecutive to: Any other sentence

Defendant Cody A. Miller in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Defendant Cody A. Miller in custody.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record. Court finds that there is a factual basis that a crime was committed and binds defendant over for trial.  Information filed.  Plea of no contest.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Court orders court costs; DNA surcharge and sample; 30 days county jail with huber and consecutive to any other sentence.  The costs are to be paid at the rate of $25.00 a month beginning 30 days after release from custody.  - rt
